Captain Elisabeth Boselli (1914-2005)
First woman figther pilot in French air force
1955: she won the 1000 Km woman speed world record for jet plane at 746 Km/h and the distance world record for jet plane: 2331 Km = 3h 30 on SNCASE Mistral (French version of De Havilland Vampire)
